			<h2><a href="http://www.dorkbot.org/dorkbotbristol/?p=46" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to B.TWEEN 07 wants your short films">B.TWEEN 07 wants your short films</a></h2>
			<h4>April 5th, 2007<!-- by Clare --> &middot; <a href="http://www.dorkbot.org/dorkbotbristol/?p=46#respond" title="Comment on B.TWEEN 07 wants your short films">No Comments</a></h4>
			<div class="entry">
				<p>Just-b. are looking for short films that explore the way interactive media (web, mobile etc) is changing our world (max 10 mins.) Selected shorts will be shown on the b.TWEEN big screen on Friday 15th June as part of b.TWEEN Interactive Media Forum.</p>
<p>b.TWEEN 07 will be hosted by National Media Museum, Bradford on the  14th–15th June. It is the gathering of the year for new media professionals, creative technologists and digital entrepreneurs.   It is the place where creativity and commerce collide.</p>
<p>b.TWEEN 06 presented a programme of over 35 international industry experts including Lord David Puttnam, Robbie Stamp (Executive Producer, Hitchhiker’s Guide to the Galaxy) and John Sanborn (Creative Director, eBay). This year’s event will be stronger than ever.</p>
<p>If you would like to show your short as part of the b.TWEEN programme, please submit a brief synopsis to Alex Walsh at alex@just-b.com by Monday 23 April (max 100 words). Selected films will be screened in standard definition.  Producers of selected works will be given free entry to the b.TWEEN forum.</p>
<p>For more information please call Alex on 0114 2210589</p>
<p><a href="http://www.just-b.com/btween" title="Just-B" onclick="javascript:urchinTracker('/outbound/www.just-b.com/btween?ref=/dorkbotbristol/index.php?paged=6');">www.just-b.com/btween</a></p>
